m. The train-save-reload loop retained 98.3% VRAM headroom. The 25% headroom gate passes.\n+\n+Project runtime/cost: `project_estimate.json` gives 2.12 / 3.53 / 7.05 charged hours (low/median/high)\n+using the repository planning model and $1.00/h assumption. Raw planned compute cost is $2.12 / $3.53 /\n+$7.05; `review_required` is false and the median is below both 10 charged hours and $35 before\n+contingency.\n+\n+Uncertainty and failure modes: the sampler smoke uses random tokens and is explicitly not a scientifically\n+valid LLC estimate; it only validates the devinterp API/performance path and trace preservation. The\n+training benchmark remains a synthetic kernel/data smoke benchmark, so the pilot must repeat timing\n+through the real data loader once implemented. Previous CUDA failures are retained in the log but are\n+not relied on for this pass; the fresh run directly observed CUDA from both `nvidia-smi` and PyTorch.\n+\n+Gate decision: proceed. Next bounded action: run the scientific pilot gate with structured Portuguese,\n+token-shuffled Portuguese, and matched English conditions; keep each long command bounded and update the\n+state files after the pilot phase.\ndiff --git a/state/experiment_registry.csv b/state/experiment_registry.csv\nindex 71fbc68..6f3b2a0 100644\n--- a/state/experiment_registry.csv\n+++ b/state/experiment_registry.csv\n@@ -3,3 +3,4 @@ infra_gate_20260620T044200Z,00_infrastructure_gate,failed,gpu_environment,ronene\n cuda_diagnostic_20260620T045329Z,00_infrastructure_gate,blocked,gpu_driver_diagnostic,roneneldan/TinyStories-3M,20260620,18cd0ebe6529a6b5fddcecad42eef2e6805cb0e5,,2026-06-20T04:53:29Z,2026-06-20T04:54:00Z,0.00,0.00,results/00_infrastructure_gate/cuda_diagnostic_20260620T045329Z,\"Short diagnostic reproduced nvidia-smi exit 9 with CUDA-enabled PyTorch 2.12.0+cu130; PCI GPU and NVIDIA modules visible but PyTorch sees 0 CUDA devices; nvidia-modprobe did not repair; stop for operator-side VM restart/reboot and official Google GPU driver installer rerun.\"\n infra_gate_20260620T050345Z,00_infrastructure_gate,blocked,cuda_preflight,roneneldan/TinyStories-3M,20260620,18cd0ebe6529a6b5fddcecad42eef2e6805cb0e5,,2026-06-20T05:03:45Z,2026-06-20T05:06:00Z,0.00,0.00,results/00_infrastructure_gate/infra_gate_20260620T050345Z,\"Fresh rerun stopped at mandated CUDA preflight: nvidia-smi exit 9; PCI GPU and NVIDIA modules visible but no /dev/nvidia0 or /dev/nvidiactl nodes observed; active /usr/bin/python3 lacks torch/transformers/datasets/devinterp/numpy/pandas; TinyStories loop, seq64/128 benchmarks, and sampler smoke not launched.\"\n cuda_worker_diag_20260620T051003Z,00_infrastructure_gate,blocked,cuda_worker_diagnostic,roneneldan/TinyStories-3M,20260620,18cd0ebe6529a6b5fddcecad42eef2e6805cb0e5,,2026-06-20T05:10:03Z,2026-06-20T05:11:00Z,0.00,0.00,results/00_infrastructure_gate/cuda_worker_diag_20260620T051003Z,\"Diagnose-and-fix tick only: active /usr/bin/python3 lacks ML stack but .venv-bench-py311 has required packages and torch 2.12.0+cu130; nvidia-smi exit 9 persists, /dev/nvidia0 and /dev/nvidiactl absent, nvidia-modprobe exits 1; check_environment classifier updated and CPU smoke tests passed; no training/sampler launched.\"\n+infra_gate_20260620T052138Z,00_infrastructure_gate,passed,gpu_environment_and_smoke_loop,roneneldan/TinyStories-3M,20260620,e2dc7f13d27a3eccdc9311d060d6741b4e697399,,2026-06-20T05:21:38Z,2026-06-20T05:24:09Z,0.0419,0.0419,results/00_infrastructure_gate/infra_gate_20260620T052138Z,\"Fresh CUDA-visible run passed: NVIDIA L4 visible to nvidia-smi and PyTorch; TinyStories-3M forward/backward and train-save-reload-evaluate-sample loop completed; seq64 mean 0.0389s/step, seq128 mean 0.0744s/step; sampler smoke 0.1410s/chain-step with 9.55MB zarr traces; minimum VRAM headroom 82.3%; project estimate median 3.53h/$3.53 and review_required=false.\"\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
